latestPosts.caption:
Paris 🇫🇷 Chanel SS2025 Show 

More Highlights from the Chanel @chanelofficial Spring/Summer 2025 Show! 🌟 Still on cloud nine—absolutely in love with the collection and the atmosphere was simply amazing! #Chanel #SS2025

The collection honors women who have liberated themselves from societal expectations, much like Gabrielle Chanel did, according to the brand. This journey is dedicated to them.

The spring/summer 2025 runway show is particularly noteworthy for Chanel, as it signifies the brand’s return to the Grand Palais after a four-year hiatus. This iconic venue, which has been a longstanding location for Chanel’s fashion presentations, has recently undergone restoration and celebrated its reopening with much excitement. Although the house is currently without a creative director, this event remains memorable for its significance.

Thank you Elodie and @chanelofficial 

#chanel #chanelgrandpalais #chanelparis #chanelparisfashionweek #chanelrunwayshow #chanelspringsummer25 #parisfashionweek

Links to all outfits are on @shop.ltk

It was our second time in Santorini, and this time we stayed in Imerovigli—it’s less crowded, just as beautiful, and the caldera views are breathtaking . Quiet mornings, breathtaking sunsets, and a more peaceful side of the island we hadn’t experienced before.

latestPosts.caption:
AAPI Reflections in The Manila Hotel #aapiheritagemonth 

As a Filipina-American, my stay  at the Manila Hotel felt deeply personal—like reconnecting with a beautiful part of my heritage. 🇵🇭✨

This iconic hotel isn’t just a landmark; it’s a living piece of Philippine history. With its rich legacy, timeless architecture, and deep cultural roots, the Manila Hotel holds stories that go far beyond its walls. Presidents, artists, and generations of Filipinos have walked these halls—and now I have, too.

In honor of AAPI Heritage Month, I’m proud to celebrate the beauty, strength, and elegance of my roots. This stay reminded me how powerful it is to embrace where you come from—and how heritage can feel both distant and deeply familiar.

If you ever visit Manila, don’t just pass by—experience the soul of the city here. ❤️
#AAPIHeritage #FilipinaPride #ManilaHotel
